classes.label: SavedObjectsErrorHelpers
description:
The SavedObjectsErrorHelpers class is a simple class for creating, decorating, and
qualifying saved object errors.

interfaces.label: AuthorizationResult
description:
The AuthorizationResult interface contains the overall status of an
authorization check, the specific authorized privileges as an
AuthorizationTypeMap, and the inaccessible objects that were restricted
due to access control.

children.label: inaccessibleObjects
description: A set of all inaccessible objects that were restricted due to access control

interfaces.label: AuthorizationTypeEntry
description:
The AuthorizationTypeEntry interface contains space-related details
for CheckAuthorizationResults.

children.label: authorizedSpaces
description:
An array of authorized spaces for the associated type/action
in the associated record/map.

children.label: isGloballyAuthorized
description: Is the associated type/action globally authorized?

interfaces.label: AuthorizeObject

The AuthorizeObject interface contains information to specify an

interfaces.label: CheckAuthorizationResult
description:
The CheckAuthorizationResult interface contains the overall status of an
authorization check and the specific authorized privileges as an
AuthorizationTypeMap.

description:
The overall status of the authorization check as a string:
'fully_authorized' | 'partially_authorized' | 'unauthorized'

children.label: typeMap

The specific authorized privileges: a map of type to record

interfaces.label: DecoratedError

The DecoratedError interface extends the Boom error object
and augments it with the 'SavedObjectsClientErrorCode' symbol

interfaces.label: EncryptedObjectDescriptor
description:
The EncryptedObjectDescriptor interface contains settings for describing
an object to be encrypted or decrpyted.

children.label: type
description: The Saved Object type

children.label: id
description: The Saved Object ID

children.label: namespace
description:
Namespace for use in index migration...
If the object is being decrypted during index migration, the object was previously
encrypted with its namespace in the descriptor portion of the AAD; on the other hand,
if the object is being decrypted during object migration, the object was never encrypted
with its namespace in the descriptor portion of the AAD.

children.label: objects
description:
The objects to authorize in order to generate the type map

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsEncryptionExtension
description:
The ISavedObjectsEncryptionExtension interface defines the functions of a saved objects
repository encryption extension. It contains functions for determining if a type is
encryptable, encrypting object attributes, and decrypting or stripping object attributes.

children.label: isEncryptableType
description: Returns true if a type has been registered as encryptable.

children.label: type
description: - the string name of the object type

returnComment: boolean, true if type is encryptable

children.label: shouldEnforceRandomId
description: Returns false if ESO type explicitly opts out of highly random UID

children.label: type
description: the string name of the object type

returnComment: boolean, true by default unless explicitly set to false

children.label: decryptOrStripResponseAttributes
description:
Given a saved object, will return a decrypted saved object or will strip
attributes from the returned object if decryption fails.

children.label: response
description: - any object R that extends SavedObject with attributes T

children.label: originalAttributes
description:
- optional, original attributes T from when the object was created (NOT encrypted).
These are used to avoid decryption execution cost if they are supplied.

returnComment: R with decrypted or stripped attributes

children.label: encryptAttributes
description:
Given a saved object descriptor and some attributes, returns an encrypted version
of supplied attributes.

children.label: descriptor
description: - an object containing a saved object id, type, and optional namespace.

children.label: attributes
description: - T, attributes of the specified object, some of which to be encrypted.

returnComment: T, encrypted attributes

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsExporter

children.label: exportByObjects

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsImporter

children.label: import
description:

detailed information.

children.label: resolveImportErrors
description:
Resolve and return saved object import errors.
See the {@link SavedObjectsResolveImportErrorsOptions | options} for more detailed information.

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsSecurityExtension
description:
The ISavedObjectsSecurityExtension interface defines the functions of a saved objects repository security extension.
It contains functions for checking & enforcing authorization, adding audit events, and redacting namespaces.

returnComment: AuthorizationResult - the resulting authorization level and authorization map

children.label: authorizeRemoveReferences
description:
Performs authorization for the REMOVE_REFERENCES security action. Checks for authorization
to delete the object to which references are to be removed. In reality, the operation is an
UPDATE to all objects that reference the given object, but the intended use for the
removeReferencesTo method is to clean up any references to an object which is being deleted
(e.g. deleting a tag).
See discussion here: https://github.com/elastic/kibana/issues/135259#issuecomment-1482515139

children.label: params
description: the namespace and object to authorize

returnComment: AuthorizationResult - the resulting authorization level and authorization map

children.label: authorizeOpenPointInTime
description: Performs authorization for the OPEN_POINT_IN_TIME security action

children.label: params
description: the namespaces and types to authorize

returnComment: AuthorizationResult - the resulting authorization level and authorization map

children.label: authorizeChangeAccessControl
description: Performs authorization for the CHANGE_OWNERSHIP or CHANGE_ACCESS_MODE security actions

children.label: params
description: the namespace and object to authorize for changing ownership

children.label: operation
description: the operation to authorize - one of 'changeAccessMode' or 'changeOwnership'

returnComment: AuthorizationResult - the resulting authorization level and authorization map

children.label: auditClosePointInTime
description: Performs audit logging for the CLOSE_POINT_IN_TIME security action

children.label: authorizeAndRedactMultiNamespaceReferences
description:
Handles all security operations for the COLLECT_MULTINAMESPACE_REFERENCES security action
Checks/enforces authorization, writes audit events, filters the object graph, and redacts spaces from the share_to_space/bulk_get
response. In other SavedObjectsRepository functions we do this before decrypting attributes. However, because of the
share_to_space/bulk_get response logic involved in deciding between the exact match or alias match, it's cleaner to do authorization,
auditing, filtering, and redaction all afterwards.

children.label: params
description: - the namespace, objects to authorize, and purpose of the operation

returnComment: SavedObjectReferenceWithContext[] - array of collected references

children.label: authorizeAndRedactInternalBulkResolve
description:
Handles all security operations for the INTERNAL_BULK_RESOLVE security action
Checks authorization, writes audit events, and redacts namespaces from the bulkResolve response. In other SavedObjectsRepository
functions we do this before decrypting attributes. However, because of the bulkResolve logic involved in deciding between the exact match
or alias match, it's cleaner to do authorization, auditing, and redaction all afterwards.

children.label: params
description: - the namespace and objects to authorize

returnComment: Array of SavedObjectsResolveResponses or BulkResolveErrors - the redacted resolve responses or errors

children.label: authorizeUpdateSpaces
description: Performs authorization for the UPDATE_OBJECTS_SPACES security action

children.label: params
description: - namespace, spacesToAdd, spacesToRemove, and objects to authorize

returnComment: AuthorizationResult - the resulting authorization level and authorization map

children.label: authorizeFind
description:
Performs authorization for the FIND security action
This method is the first of two security steps for the find operation (saved objects repository's find method)
This method should be called first in order to provide data needed to construct the type-to-namespace map for the search DSL

children.label: params
description: - namespaces and types to authorize

returnComment: AuthorizationResult - the resulting authorization level and authorization map

children.label: getFindRedactTypeMap
description:
Gets an updated type map for redacting results of the FIND security action
This method is the second of two security steps for the find operation (saved objects repository's find method)
This method should be called last in order to update the type map used to redact namespaces in the results

children.label: params
description: - namespace, spacesToAdd, spacesToRemove, and objects to authorize

returnComment: - the updated type map used for redaction

children.label: redactNamespaces
description: Filters a saved object's spaces based on an authorization map (from CheckAuthorizationResult)

children.label: params
description: - the saved object and an authorization map

returnComment: SavedObject - saved object with filtered spaces

children.label: authorizeDisableLegacyUrlAliases
description:
Performs authorization for the disableLegacyUrlAliases method of the SecureSpacesClientWrapper
There is no return for this method. If unauthorized the method with throw, otherwise will resolve.

children.label: aliases
description: - array of legacy url alias targets

children.label: auditObjectsForSpaceDeletion
description: Performs saved object audit logging for the delete method of the SecureSpacesClientWrapper

children.label: spaceId
description: - the id of the space being deleted

children.label: objects
description: - the objects to audit

children.label: getCurrentUser
description: Retrieves the current user from the request context if available

children.label: includeSavedObjectNames
description: Retrieves whether we need to include save objects names in the audit out

; }, R extends { type: string; id: string; esRequestIndex?: number | undefined; }>(expectedResults:

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsSerializer

A serializer that can be used to manually convert {@link SavedObjectsRawDoc | raw} or
{@link SavedObjectSanitizedDoc | sanitized} documents to the other kind.

description: Determines whether the raw document can be converted to a saved object.

children.label: doc
description: - The raw ES document to be tested

children.label: options
description: - Options for parsing the raw document.

children.label: rawToSavedObject

children.label: doc
description: - The raw ES document to be converted to saved object format.

children.label: options
description: - Options for parsing the raw document.

children.label: savedObjectToRaw
description: Converts a document from the saved object client format to the format that is stored in elasticsearch.

children.label: savedObj
description: - The saved object to be converted to raw ES format.

children.label: generateRawId

signature: (namespace: string | undefined, type: string, id: string) => string

children.label: namespace

children.label: type
description: - The saved object type

children.label: id

children.label: generateRawLegacyUrlAliasId
description: Given a saved object type and id, generates the compound id that is stored in the raw document for its legacy URL alias.
signature: (namespace: string | undefined, type: string, id: string) => string

children.label: namespace
description: - The namespace of the saved object

children.label: type
description: - The saved object type

children.label: id

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsSpacesExtension
description:
The ISavedObjectsSpacesExtension interface defines the functions of a saved objects repository spaces extension.
It contains functions for getting the current namespace & getting and array of searchable spaces.

children.label: getCurrentNamespace
description:
Retrieves the active namespace ID. This is *not* the same as a namespace string. See also: `namespaceIdToString` and
`namespaceStringToId`.

This takes the saved objects repository's namespace option as a parameter, and doubles as a validation function; if the namespace
option has already been set some other way, this will throw an error.

children.label: getSearchableNamespaces
description:
Given a list of namespace strings, returns a subset that the user is authorized to search in.
If a wildcard '*' is used, it is expanded to an explicit list of namespace strings.

children.label: asScopedToNamespace
description: Returns a new Saved Objects Spaces Extension scoped to the specified namespace.

children.label: namespace
description: Space to which the extension should be scoped to.

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectTypeRegistry
description: Registry holding information about all the registered {@link SavedObjectsType | saved object types}.

children.label: getLegacyTypes
description: Return legacy types, this types can't be registered

children.label: getType
description: Return the {@link SavedObjectsType | type} definition for given type name.

children.label: getVisibleTypes
description:
Returns all visible {@link SavedObjectsType | types}.

A visible type is a type that doesn't explicitly define `hidden=true` during registration.

children.label: getVisibleToHttpApisTypes
description:
Returns all visible {@link SavedObjectsType | types} exposed to the global SO HTTP APIs

A visibleToHttpApis type is a type that doesn't explicitly define `hidden=true` nor `hiddenFromHttpApis=true` during registration.

children.label: getAllTypes
description:
Return all {@link SavedObjectsType | types} currently registered, including the hidden ones.

To only get the visible types (which is the most common use case), use `getVisibleTypes` instead.

children.label: getImportableAndExportableTypes
description: Return all {@link SavedObjectsType | types} currently registered that are importable/exportable.

interfaces.label: SavedObject
description: Definition of the Saved Object interface

children.label: id
description: The ID of this Saved Object, guaranteed to be unique for all objects of the same `type`

children.label: type
description: The type of Saved Object. Each plugin can define its own custom Saved Object types.

children.label: version
description: An opaque version number which changes on each successful write operation. Can be used for implementing optimistic concurrency control.

children.label: created_at
description: Timestamp of the time this document had been created.

children.label: created_by
description: The ID of the user who created this object.

children.label: updated_at
description: Timestamp of the last time this document had been updated.

children.label: updated_by
description: The ID of the user who last updated this object.

children.label: error
description: Error associated with this object, populated if an operation failed for this object.

children.label: attributes
description: The data for a Saved Object is stored as an object in the `attributes` property.

children.label: references
description: {@inheritdoc SavedObjectReference}

children.label: migrationVersion
description: {@inheritdoc SavedObjectsMigrationVersion}

children.label: coreMigrationVersion
description: A semver value that is used when upgrading objects between Kibana versions.

children.label: typeMigrationVersion
description: A semver value that is used when migrating documents between Kibana versions.

children.label: namespaces
description:
Space(s) that this saved object exists in. This attribute is not used for "global" saved object types which are registered with
`namespaceType: 'agnostic'`.

children.label: originId
description:
The ID of the saved object this originated from. This is set if this object's `id` was regenerated; that can happen during migration
from a legacy single-namespace type, or during import. It is only set during migration or create operations. This is used during import
to ensure that ID regeneration is deterministic, so saved objects will be overwritten if they are imported multiple times into a given
space.

children.label: managed
description:
Flag indicating if a saved object is managed by Kibana (default=false)

This can be leveraged by applications to e.g. prevent edits to a managed
saved object. Instead, users can be guided to create a copy first and
make their edits to the copy.

children.label: accessControl
description:
Access control information of the saved object.
This can be be used to customize access to the object in addition to RBAC, e.g.
to set an object to read-only mode, where it is only editable by the owner of
the object (or an admin), even if other users are granted write access via a role.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectAccessControl
description: Definition of the Saved Object access control interface

children.label: owner
description: The ID of the user who owns this object.

children.label: accessMode
description:
The access mode of the object. `write_restricted` is editable only by the owner and admin users.
Access mode `default` is editable by all users with write access to the object.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectAttributes
description:
The data for a Saved Object is stored as an object in the `attributes`
property.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectDoc

children.label: request

children.label: includeReferencesDeep
description: flag to also include all related saved objects in the export stream.

children.label: includeNamespaces
description:
Flag to also include namespace information in the export stream. By default, namespace information is not included in exported objects.
This is only intended to be used internally during copy-to-space operations, and it is not exposed as an option for the external HTTP
route for exports.

children.label: excludeExportDetails
description: flag to not append {@link SavedObjectsExportResultDetails | export details} to the end of the export stream.

children.label: namespace
description: optional namespace to override the namespace used by the savedObjectsClient.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectMigrationMap
description:
A map of {@link SavedObjectMigration | migrations} to be used for a given type.
The map's keys must be valid semver versions, and they cannot exceed the current Kibana version.

For a given document, only migrations with a higher version number than that of the document will be applied.
Migrations are executed in order, starting from the lowest version and ending with the highest one.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsFullModelVersion
description:
Represents a model version of a given saved object type.

Model versions supersede the {@link SavedObjectsType.migrations | migrations} (and {@link SavedObjectsType.schemas | schemas}) APIs
by exposing an unified way of describing the changes of shape or data of a type.

children.label: changes
description:
The list of changes associated with this version.

Model version changes are defined via low-level components, allowing to use composition
to describe the list of changes bound to a given version.

children.label: schemas
description:
The {@link SavedObjectsModelVersionSchemaDefinitions | schemas} associated with this version.

Schemas are used to validate / convert the shape and/or content of the documents at various stages of their usages.
Required for rollback safety

children.label: forwardCompatibility
description:
The schema applied when retrieving documents of a higher version from the cluster.
Used for multi-version compatibility in managed environments.

When retrieving a savedObject document from an index, if the version of the document
is higher than the latest version known of the Kibana instance, the document will go
through the `forwardCompatibility` schema of the associated model version.

E.g a Kibana instance with model version `2` for type `foo` types fetches a `foo` document
at model version `3`. The document will then go through the `forwardCompatibility`
of the model version 2 (if present).

See {@link SavedObjectModelVersionForwardCompatibilitySchema} for more info.

children.label: create
description:
The schema applied when creating a document of the current version
Allows for validating properties using @kbn/config-schema validations

children.label: createNewCopies

children.label: refresh

children.label: compatibilityMode

different Kibana versions (e.g. generate legacy URL aliases for all imported objects that have to change IDs).

children.label: managed
description:
If true, will import as a managed object, else will import as not managed.

This can be leveraged by applications to e.g. prevent edits to a managed
saved object. Instead, users can be guided to create a copy first and
make their edits to the copy.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsType
description: Definition of a type of savedObject.

children.label: name
description: The name of the type, which is also used as the internal id.

children.label: nameAttribute
description: The attribute path to the saved object's name

children.label: hidden
description:
Is the type hidden by default. If true, repositories will not have access to this type unless explicitly
declared as an `extraType` when creating the repository.
It is recommended to hide the type for better backward compatibility.
The hidden types will not be automatically exposed via the HTTP API.
Therefore, that should prevent unexpected behavior in the client code, as all the interactions will be done via the plugin API.

Hidden types must be listed to be accessible by the client.

(await context.core).savedObjects.getClient({ includeHiddenTypes: [MY_PLUGIN_HIDDEN_SAVED_OBJECT_TYPE] })

See {@link SavedObjectsServiceStart.createInternalRepository | createInternalRepository}.

children.label: hiddenFromHttpApis
description:
Is the type hidden from the http APIs. If `hiddenFromHttpApis:true`, repositories will have access to the type but the type is not exposed via the HTTP APIs.
It is recommended to hide types registered with 'hidden=false' from the httpApis for backward compatibility in the HTTP layer.

children.label: namespaceType
description: The {@link SavedObjectsNamespaceType | namespace type} for the type.

children.label: indexPattern
description: If defined, the type instances will be stored in the given index instead of the default one.

children.label: convertToAliasScript
description: If defined, will be used to convert the type to an alias.

children.label: excludeOnUpgrade
description:
If defined, allows a type to exclude unneeded documents from the migration process and effectively be deleted.
See {@link SavedObjectTypeExcludeFromUpgradeFilterHook} for more details.

children.label: mappings
description: The {@link SavedObjectsTypeMappingDefinition | mapping definition} for the type.

children.label: migrations
description:
An optional map of {@link SavedObjectMigrationFn | migrations} or a function returning a map of
{@link SavedObjectMigrationFn | migrations} to be used to migrate the type.

children.label: schemas
description:
An optional schema that can be used to validate the attributes of the type.

When provided, calls to {@link SavedObjectsClient.create | create} will be validated against this schema.

See {@link SavedObjectsValidationMap} for more details.

children.label: convertToMultiNamespaceTypeVersion
description:
If defined, objects of this type will be converted to a 'multiple' or 'multiple-isolated' namespace type when migrating to
this version.

Requirements:

 1. This string value must be a valid semver version
 2. This type must have previously specified {@link SavedObjectsNamespaceType | `namespaceType: 'single'`}
 3. This type must also specify {@link SavedObjectsNamespaceType | `namespaceType: 'multiple'`} *or*
    {@link SavedObjectsNamespaceType | `namespaceType: 'multiple-isolated'`}

Example of a single-namespace type in 7.12:

```ts
{
  name: 'foo',
  hidden: false,
  namespaceType: 'single',
  mappings: {...}
}
```

Example after converting to a multi-namespace (isolated) type in 8.0:

```ts
{
  name: 'foo',
  hidden: false,
  namespaceType: 'multiple-isolated',
  mappings: {...},
  convertToMultiNamespaceTypeVersion: '8.0.0'
}
```

Example after converting to a multi-namespace (shareable) type in 8.1:

```ts
{
  name: 'foo',
  hidden: false,
  namespaceType: 'multiple',
  mappings: {...},
  convertToMultiNamespaceTypeVersion: '8.0.0'
}
```

Note: migration function(s) can be optionally specified for any of these versions and will not interfere with the conversion process.

children.label: management
description: An optional {@link SavedObjectsTypeManagementDefinition | saved objects management section} definition for the type.

children.label: modelVersions
description:
A map of model versions associated with this type.

Model versions supersede the {@link SavedObjectsType.migrations | migrations} (and {@link SavedObjectsType.schemas | schemas}) APIs
by exposing an unified way of describing the changes of shape or data of the type.

Model versioning is decoupled from Kibana versioning, and isolated between types.
Model versions are identified by a single numeric value, starting at `1` and without gaps.

Please refer to {@link SavedObjectsModelVersion} for more details on the model version API.

children.label: getTitle
description:
Function returning the title to display in the management table.
If not defined, will use the object's type and id to generate a label.

children.label: supportsAccessControl
description:
If defined and set to `true`, this saved object type will support access control functionality.

When enabled, objects of this type can have an `accessControl` property containing:
- `owner`: The ID of the user who owns this object
- `accessMode`: Access mode setting, supports 'write_restricted' or 'default'.

This property works in conjunction with the SavedObjectAccessControl interface defined
in server_types.ts.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsTypeManagementDefinition
description: Configuration options for the {@link SavedObjectsType | type}'s management section.

children.label: importableAndExportable
description: Is the type importable or exportable. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: displayName
description: When specified, will be used instead of the type's name in SO management section's labels.

children.label: visibleInManagement
description:
When set to false, the type will not be listed or searchable in the SO management section.
Main usage of setting this property to false for a type is when objects from the type should
be included in the export via references or export hooks, but should not directly appear in the SOM.
Defaults to `true`.

children.label: defaultSearchField
description: The default search field to use for this type. Defaults to `id`.

children.label: icon
description:
The eui icon name to display in the management table.
If not defined, the default icon will be used.

children.label: getTitle
description:
Function returning the title to display in the management table.
If not defined, will use the object's type and id to generate a label.

children.label: getEditUrl
description:
Function returning the url to use to redirect to the editing page of this object.
If not defined, editing will not be allowed.

children.label: getInAppUrl
description:
Function returning the url to use to redirect to this object from the management section.
If not defined, redirecting to the object will not be allowed.
signature: <Attributes>) => { path: string; uiCapabilitiesPath: string; } | undefined) | undefined
returnComment:
undefined or an object containing a `path` and `uiCapabilitiesPath` properties. the `path` is the path to
the object page, relative to the base path. `uiCapabilitiesPath` is the path to check in the
{@link Capabilities | uiCapabilities} to check if the user has permission to access the object.

children.label: onExport
description:
An optional export transform function that can be used transform the objects of the registered type during
the export process.

It can be used to either mutate the exported objects, or add additional objects (of any type) to the export list.

See {@link SavedObjectsExportTransform | the transform type documentation} for more info and examples.

When implementing both `isExportable` and `onExport`, it is mandatory that
`isExportable` returns the same value for an object before and after going
though the export transform.
E.g `isExportable(objectBeforeTransform) === isExportable(objectAfterTransform)`

children.label: onImport
description:
An optional {@link SavedObjectsImportHook | import hook} to use when importing given type.

Import hooks are executed during the savedObjects import process and allow to interact
with the imported objects. See the {@link SavedObjectsImportHook | hook documentation}
for more info.

children.label: isExportable
description:
Optional hook to specify whether an object should be exportable.

If specified, `isExportable` will be called during export for each
of this type's objects in the export, and the ones not matching the
predicate will be excluded from the export.

When implementing both `isExportable` and `onExport`, it is mandatory that
`isExportable` returns the same value for an object before and after going
though the export transform.
E.g `isExportable(objectBeforeTransform) === isExportable(objectAfterTransform)`

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsTypeMappingDefinition
description: Describe a saved object type mapping.

children.label: dynamic
description:
The dynamic property of the mapping, either `false` or `'strict'`. If
unspecified `dynamic: 'strict'` will be inherited from the top-level
index mappings.

children.label: properties
description: The underlying properties of the type mapping

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsValidationMap
description:
A map of {@link SavedObjectsValidationSpec | validation specs} to be used for a given type.
The map's keys must be valid semver versions.

Any time you change the schema of a {@link SavedObjectsType}, you should add a new entry
to this map for the Kibana version the change was introduced in.

interfaces.label: SetAccessControlToWriteParams
description:
The SetAccessControlToWriteParams interface defines the parameters for the setAccessControlToWrite
function. It includes the incoming access control mode, saved object type, the createdBy
(current user profile ID if it exists), and the accessControl attributes from the prfelight check.

children.label: accessMode
description: The access control mode (default | write_restricted)

children.label: type
description: The saved object type

children.label: createdBy
description: The relevant user profile ID for the operation - used in create and bulk create

children.label: preflightAccessControl
description: The existing access control metadata from the operation's preflight check

misc.label: AuthorizationTypeMap
description:
The AuthorizationTypeMap type is a map of saved object type
to a record of action/AuthorizationTypeEntry,

misc.label: AuthorizeOpenPointInTimeParams
description:
The AuthorizeOpenPointInTimeParams interface is used for the
AuthorizeOpenPointInTime method of the ISavedObjectsSecurityExtension.
It is identical to AuthorizeFindParams.

misc.label: MAIN_SAVED_OBJECT_INDEX
description:
Collect and centralize the names of the different saved object indices.
Note that all of them start with the '.kibana' prefix.
There are multiple places in the code that these indices have the form .kibana*.
However, beware that there are some system indices that have the same prefix
but are NOT used to store saved objects, e.g.: .kibana_security_session_1

misc.label: ModelVersionIdentifier
description:
A record of {@link SavedObjectsModelVersion | model versions} for a given savedObjects type.
The record's keys must be integers, starting with 1 for the first entry, and there shouldn't be gaps.

misc.label: SavedObjectAttribute
description: Type definition for a Saved Object attribute value

misc.label: SavedObjectAttributeSingle
description: Don't use this type, it's simply a helper type for {@link SavedObjectAttribute}

misc.label: SavedObjectMigration
description:
Saved Objects migration.
It can be either a {@link SavedObjectMigrationFn | migration function} or a {@link SavedObjectMigrationParams | migration object}.

misc.label: SavedObjectMigrationFn
description:
A migration function for a {@link SavedObjectsType | saved object type}
used to migrate it to a given version

misc.label: SavedObjectModelDataBackfillFn
description: A data backfill function associated with a {@link SavedObjectsModelDataBackfillChange | data backfill} change.

misc.label: SavedObjectModelTransformationDoc
description: Document type used during model migration.

misc.label: SavedObjectModelTransformationFn
description:
Transformation function for the model version API.

Similar to the old migration system, model version transformations take the document to migrate
and a context object as input and must return the transformed document in its return value.

misc.label: SavedObjectModelUnsafeTransformFn
description: A data transformation function associated with a {@link SavedObjectsModelUnsafeTransformChange | unsafe transform} change.

misc.label: SavedObjectModelVersionForwardCompatibilityFn
description: Plain javascript function alternative for {@link SavedObjectModelVersionForwardCompatibilitySchema}

misc.label: SavedObjectModelVersionForwardCompatibilityObjectSchema
description: Object-schema (from `@kbn/config-schema`) alternative for {@link SavedObjectModelVersionForwardCompatibilitySchema}

misc.label: SavedObjectModelVersionForwardCompatibilitySchema
description:
Schema used when retrieving a document of a higher version to convert them to the older version.

These schemas can be defined in multiple ways:
- A `@kbn/config-schema`'s Object schema, that will receive the document's attributes
- An arbitrary function that will receive the document's attributes as parameter and should return the converted attributes

misc.label: SavedObjectSanitizedDoc
description:
Describes Saved Object documents that have passed through the migration
framework and are guaranteed to have a `references` root property.

misc.label: SavedObjectsClientFactory
description: Describes the factory used to create instances of the Saved Objects Client.
signature: <unknown, unknown, unknown, any>; includedHiddenTypes?: string[] | undefined; extensions?:
<unknown, unknown, unknown, any>; includedHiddenTypes?: string[] | undefined; extensions?:

misc.label: SavedObjectsClientFactoryProvider
description: Provider to invoke to retrieve a {@link SavedObjectsClientFactory}.

misc.label: SavedObjectsEncryptionExtensionFactory
description: Describes the factory used to create instances of the Saved Objects Encryption Extension.

misc.label: SavedObjectsExportTransform
description:
Transformation function used to mutate the exported objects of the associated type.

A type's export transform function will be executed once per user-initiated export,
for all objects of that type.

misc.label: SavedObjectsExtensionFactory
description: Describes the base Saved Objects Extension factory.

misc.label: SavedObjectsFieldMapping
SavedObjectsImportHook
description:
A hook associated with a specific saved object type, that will be invoked during
the import process. The hook will have access to the objects of the registered type.

Currently, the only supported feature for import hooks is to return warnings to be displayed
in the UI when the import succeeds.

misc.label: SavedObjectsModelChange
SavedObjectsModelVersionMapProvider
description:
A function returning a {@link SavedObjectsModelVersionMap | model version map}

Ensured to be called after all plugins executed their `setup` phase.
Similar to what was done with migrations, can be used to defer resolving the model versions
associated to a type to after all plugins have been set up.

misc.label: SavedObjectsSecurityExtensionFactory
description: Describes the factory used to create instances of the Saved Objects Security Extension.

misc.label: SavedObjectsSpacesExtensionFactory
description: Describes the factory used to create instances of the Saved Objects Spaces Extension.

misc.label: SavedObjectsValidationSpec
description: Allows for validating properties using @kbn/config-schema validations.

misc.label: SavedObjectTypeExcludeFromUpgradeFilterHook
description:
If defined, allows a type to run a search query and return a query filter that may match any documents which may
be excluded from the next migration upgrade process. Useful for cleaning up large numbers of old documents which
are no longer needed and may slow the migration process.

If this hook fails, the migration will proceed without these documents having been filtered out, so this
should not be used as a guarantee that these documents have been deleted.

misc.label: SavedObjectUnsanitizedDoc
description:
Describes Saved Object documents from Kibana < 7.0.0 which don't have a
`references` root property defined. This type should only be used in
migrations.
